 &lt;p&gt;Predicting transcriptional outcomes of novel multigene perturbations with GEARS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span id=&#34;more&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;å®žéªŒç›®çš„ï¼šUnderstanding cellular responses to genetic perturbation is central to numerous biomedical application, from identifying genetic interations involved in cancer to developing methods for regenerative medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;æŒ‘æˆ˜ï¼š The combinatorial explosion in the number of possible multigene perturbations severely limits experimental interrogation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GEARS: graph-enhanced gene activation and repression simulator. A method that integrates deep learning with a knowledge graph of gene-gene relationships to predict transcriptional responses to both single and multigene perturbations using single-cell RNA-sequencing data from perturbational screens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;è¿™æ®µè¯ä¸æ˜¯å¾ˆç†è§£ï¼šThe screens were run using the Perturb-seq assay, which combines a pooled screen with a single-cell RNA-sequencing readout of the entire transcriptome for each cell. ä»€ä¹ˆæ˜¯ Perturb-seq assayï¼Œä»€ä¹ˆåˆæ˜¯ pooled screen&lt;/p&gt;
